{"itemid":1285,"subject":"Dangerous Virgins","event":"Tor.com has just posted another teaser from our forthcoming DANGEROUS WOMEN anthology, this one an except from Diana Gabaldon&#39;s story, &quot;Virgins.&quot;\r\n\r\nYou can check it out here:&nbsp; http://www.tor.com/stories/2013/07/dangerous-women-diana-gabaldon-excerpt\r\n\r\nAnd yes, this story is part of Diana&#39;s bestselling and award-winning OUTLANDER sequence.\r\n\r\nDANGEROUS WOMEN will be published on December 3, but is available for advance purchase now from your favorite online bookseller.\r\n\r\nThe full table of contents:\r\nINTRODUCTION, by Gardner Dozois\r\nSOME DESPERADO, by Joe Abercrombie\r\nMY HEART IS EITHER BROKEN, by Megan Abbott\r\nNORA&rsquo;S SONG, by Cecelia Holland\r\nTHE HANDS THAT ARE NOT THERE, by Melinda Snodgrass\r\nBOMBSHELLS, by Jim Butcher\r\nRAISA STEPANOVA, by Carrie Vaughn\r\nWRESTLING JESUS, by Joe R. Lansdale\r\nNEIGHBORS, by Megan Lindholm\r\nI KNOW HOW TO PICK &lsquo;EM, by Lawrence Block\r\nSHADOWS FOR SILENCE IN THE FORESTS OF HELL, by Brandon Sanderson\r\nA QUEEN IN EXILE, by Sharon Kay Penman\r\nTHE GIRL IN THE MIRROR, by Lev Grossman\r\nSECOND ARABESQUE, VERY SLOWLY, by Nancy Kress\r\nCITY LAZARUS, by Diana Rowland\r\nVIRGINS, by Diana Gabaldon\r\nHELL HATH NO FURY, by Sherilynn Kenyon\r\nPRONOUNCING DOOM, by S.M. Stirling\r\nNAME THE BEAST, by Sam Sykes\r\nCARETAKERS, by Pat Cadigan\r\nLIES MY MOTHER TOLD ME, by Caroline Spector\r\nTHE PRINCESS AND THE QUEEN, by George R.R. Martin","ditemid":329110,"eventtime":"2013-07-25 18:41:00","props":{"current_location":"Santa Fe","taglist":"tor, anthologies","current_moodid":109,"commentalter":1374979869,"opt_lockcomments":1,"picture_keyword":"Ashford","opt_screening":"F","personifi_tags":"nterms:no","interface":"web","revnum":1,"revtime":1375043314},"can_comment":0,"logtime":"2013-07-26 00:41:12","anum":150,"url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/329110.html","event_timestamp":1374777660,"reply_count":11,"comments":[{"shown":1,"collapsed":0,"actions":[{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/329110.html?thread=18016918#t18016918","name":"permalink","title":"link"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/329110.html?thread=18016918#t18016918","name":"collapse","title":"Collapse"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/329110.html?thread=18016918#t18016918","name":"expand","title":"Expand"}],"uname":"indianveela","loaded":1,"p_tracked":0,"commenter_journal_base":"http://indianveela.livejournal.com/","statprefix":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net","dtalkid":18016918,"talkid":70378,"thread_url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/329110.html?thread=18016918#t18016918","upictitle":"indianveela: pic#0","article":"Hi, George! I plan on making Dangerous Women my first cross genre anthology. I can't wait to read the stories. But, I have a question for you: do you prefer writing long, all-encompassing epics (you know what I'm talking about :)),or do you prefer the the more subdued manageability of the novella/short story?","siteroot":"http://www.livejournal.com","poster":"grrm","stime":"3 years ago","ctime":"July 26 2013, 02:02:54 UTC","massactions":0,"subject":"Quick Question","deleted":0,"username":[{"journal_url":"http://indianveela.livejournal.com/","striked":null,"journaltype":"P","userhead_url":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net/img/userinfo_v8.svg?v=17080?v=146.10","color":null,"noctxpopup":0,"side_alias":0,"journal":"indianveela","inline_css":0,"attrs":null,"is_identity":0,"bold":1,"show_userhead":1,"username":"indianveela","user_alias":"","profile_url":"http://indianveela.livejournal.com/profile","alias":0}],"dname":"indianveela","ctime_ts":1374804174,"tracked":0},{"shown":1,"collapsed":0,"actions":[{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/329110.html?thread=18019734#t18019734","name":"permalink","title":"link"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/329110.html?thread=18019734#t18019734","name":"collapse","title":"Collapse"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grr