popup":0,"side_alias":0,"journal":"sourbillytipton","inline_css":0,"attrs":null,"is_identity":0,"bold":1,"show_userhead":1,"username":"sourbillytipton","user_alias":"","profile_url":"http://sourbillytipton.livejournal.com/profile","alias":0}],"etime":"July 26 2013, 19:10:35 UTC","dname":"sourbillytipton","ctime_ts":1374865601,"tracked":0},{"shown":1,"collapsed":0,"actions":[{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/329110.html?thread=18022294#t18022294","name":"permalink","title":"link"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/329110.html?thread=18022294#t18022294","name":"collapse","title":"Collapse"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/329110.html?thread=18022294#t18022294","name":"expand","title":"Expand"}],"uname":"goldensinger943","loaded":1,"p_tracked":0,"commenter_journal_base":"http://goldensinger943.livejournal.com/","statprefix":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net","dtalkid":18022294,"talkid":70399,"thread_url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/329110.html?thread=18022294#t18022294","above":18022038,"upictitle":"goldensinger943: pic#0","article":"Hi GRRM, I'm a huge fan. I spend a good portion of my days thinking about ASoIaF. Once, I recall, when recommending your series to a friend, I mentioned that I had spent the last four hours online reading about a possible conspiracy theory relating to the actions of some of the characters, as evidence of how absorbing the books can be. The books are so incredibly detailed that I often find myself getting lost in them. And like many others, I spend the rest of my time patiently waiting for The Winds of Winter.<br /><br />Anyway, regarding Indira's casting, didn't you recently say that the Martells (Dornish) were, essentially, white (Mediterranean)? Indira, as half Indian and half Swiss (I think?) is going to be perceived as a person of colour on Game of Thrones, unlike Pascal who some have said may be white-passing. I know that Ellaria is only half Dornish, but many have long suspected that the Dornish may have some Middle Eastern or South Asian equivalents in the real world (I think you once also mentioned that Janina Gavankar matched your view of Lady Nymeria (half Salty Dornish, half-Volantene)).<br /><br />I realize that you have, to some extent, already discussed this, but in light of Indira's casting and your comment about Gavankar (which I recently heard about since this whole Oberyn Martell debate began), I was hoping you would consider the matter once more. And again, thank you for making this series. I never thought I'd spend this much time thinking about a single series of books...","siteroot":"http://www.livejournal.com","poster":"grrm","stime":"3 years ago","below":18026646,"ctime":"July 26 2013, 21:10:38 UTC","parent":18021526,"massactions":0,"subject":"Re: &quot;ROME&quot;","deleted":0,"username":[{"journal_url":"http://goldensinger943.livejournal.com/","striked":null,"journaltype":"P","userhead_url":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net/img/userinfo_v8.svg?v=17080?v=146.10","color":null,"noctxpopup":0,"side_alias":0,"journal":"goldensinger943","inline_css":0,"attrs":null,"is_identity":0,"bold":1,"show_userhead":1,"username":"goldensinger943","user_alias":"","profile_url":"http://goldensinger943.livejournal.com/profile","alias":0}],"dname":"goldensinger943","ctime_ts":1374873038,"tracked":0},{"shown":1,"collapsed":0,"userpic":"http://l-userpic.livejournal.com/91237832/7059164","actions":[{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/329110.html?thread=18022550#t18022550","name":"permalink","title":"link"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/329110.html?thread=18022550#t18022550","name":"collapse","title":"Collapse"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/329110.html?thread=18022550#t18022550","name":"expand","title":"Expand"}],"uname":"grrm","loaded":1,"p_tracked":0,"commenter_journal_base":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/","statprefix":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net","dtalkid":18022550,"talkid":70400,"thread_url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/329110.html?thread=18022550#t18022550","above":18022294,"upictitle":"George R.R. Martin: Spain","article":"Ellaria Sand is the natural (that is to say, bastard) daughter of Lord Uller of Hellholt.  The Ullers are \"sandy Dornish\" and generally darker than the \"salty Dornish\" like the Martells.  So this is perfectly consistent with the books.<br /><br />More importantly, however, Indira Varma is an amazing and talented actress.  THAT's what matters.  She will be a great Ellaria Sand.<br /><br />And with that, I have said all I said about this subject.  I am all in favor of diversity... in my books, in the TV show, and especially in the real world... but when the debate goes beyond race (itself a dubious and artificial construct) and ethnicity to debate the precise shade of an actor's skin, that's too damn far.  ","siteroot":"http://www.livejournal.com","poster":"grrm","stime":"3 years ago","ctime":"July 27 2013, 00:03:55 UTC","parent":18022294,"massactions":0,"subject":"Re: &quot;ROME&quot;","deleted":0,"username":[{"journal_url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/","striked":null,"journaltype":"P","userhead_url":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net/img/userinfo_v8.svg?v=17080?v=146.10","color":null,"noctxpopup":0,"side_alias":0,"journal":"grrm","inline_css":0,"attrs":null,"is_identity":0,"bold":1,"show_userhead":1,"username":"grrm","user_alias":"","profile_url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/profile","alias":0}],"dname":"grrm","ctime_ts":1374883435,"tracked":0},{"shown":1,"collapsed":0,"actions":[{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/329110.html?thread=18023318#t18023318","name":"permalink","title":"link"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/329110.html?thread=18023318#t18023318","name":"collapse","title":"Collapse"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/329110.html?thread=18023318#t18023318","name":"expand","title":"Expand"}],"uname":"st_croixboston","loaded":1,"p_tracked":0,"commenter_journal_base":"http://st-croixboston.livejournal.com/","statprefix":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net","dtalkid":18023318,"talkid":70403,"thread_url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/329110.html?thread=18023318#t18023318","above":18022550,"upictitle":"st_croixboston: pic#0","article":"Hello,<br />I love the casting and she will portray a great Ellaria Sands. It's a fantasy world and the casting department has done a great job since the 1st season and I trust they will continue too.<br />Not even sure where this became an issue. As I read the books the description is there , but its more about the characters development and their involvement in the game. are they bystanders, are they pawns,or are they  players/contenders. <br />I'm just reading your interviews and blog and shake my head when see this come up AGAIN and you have  to comment again. It must be frustrating because its not about the color of the skin it's about the character involvement and actors skills portraying your characters.. Which they have done amazing.<br />Thank you for many hours of  reading and entertainment. Love the world of Ice and Fire. Hope to se you in Boston on The Winds of Winter book tour,<br />Patrick<br />","siteroot":"http://www.livejournal.com","poster":"grrm","stime":"3 years ago","ctime":"July 27 2013, 03:38:34 UTC","parent":18022550,"massactions":0,"subject":"Re: &quot;ROME&quot;","deleted":0,"username":[{"journal_url":"http://st-croixboston.livejournal.com/","striked":null,"journaltype":"P","userhead_url":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net/img/userinfo_v8.svg?v=17080?v=146.10","color":null,"noctxpopup":0,"side_alias":0,"journal":"st_croixboston","inline_css":0,"attrs":null,"is_identity":0,"bold":1,"show_userhead":1,"username":"st_croixboston","user_alias":"","profile_url":"http://st-croixboston.livejournal.com/profile","alias":0}],"dname":"st_croixboston","ctime_ts":1374896314,"tracked":0},{"shown":1,"collapsed":0,"actions":[{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/329110.html?thread=18026646#t18026646","name":"permal